keywords  : edit, redit, medit, oedit, tedit, dedit, zedit, socedit, hedit
info      :~
  Please see help OLC for all available commands.
  
  As a builder, you can create and modify zone content using the edit commands.
  These commands provide interactive interfaces for designing rooms, objects,
  mobiles, triggers, dialogs, socials, zones, and help files. There is an edit
  command for each major type of content.
  
  edit commands are: redit, medit, oedit, tedit, dedit, zedit, socedit, and hedit.
  Syntax is as follows: <edit command> <reference>
  
  If the reference does not exist, a new prototype will be created. If it
  exists, you will edit the existing prototype.
  
  Examples:
    redit tavern         - Edit or create room prototype 'tavern'
    medit guard          - Edit or create mobile prototype 'guard'
    oedit sword          - Edit or create object prototype 'sword'
    tedit death_trigger  - Edit or create trigger prototype 'death_trigger'
    dedit shop_dialog    - Edit or create dialog prototype 'shop_dialog'
    zedit fooland        - Edit zone 'fooland'
    socedit smile        - Edit or create social 'smile'
    hedit OLC            - Edit or create help file 'OLC'
  
  To create a new zone, use: zedit new <zone key>
user_group: builder
-
